    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-12-06T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-12-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="498"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d498">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <gloss target="#t_JCS1">J. C. S.</gloss> Files</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Note by the Secretaries of the Combined Chiefs of Staff</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <gloss target="#t_CCS1">C. C. S.</gloss> 401/2</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-12-06">6 December
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <gloss target="#t_VLR1">V. L. R.</gloss>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Airfields</hi> (<gloss target="#t_B291">B–29</gloss>) <hi
                        rend="smallcaps">in the China–Burma–India Area</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The Combined Chiefs of Staff have agreed to the following interpretation of
                    paragraph 3 of <gloss target="#t_CCS1">C.C.S.</gloss> 401/1:<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d498fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_377">p. 377</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“If the necessary work in India is to be completed by the desired date of
                        April first, it is essential that United States units and equipment required
                        should arrive in Calcutta by the 15th of January and, in addition, that
                        certain resources be diverted from Ledo, which would <pb facs="0914" n="810"
                            xml:id="pg_810"/> result in delaying progress of road construction for a
                        period of six weeks to two months.</p>
                    <p>“Certain preparatory work in advance of arrival of American units and
                        equipment can be done without interfering with <gloss target="#t_SEAC1">S.
                            E. A. C.</gloss> projects, which, with arrival of necessary resources
                        from the U. S. by January 15th, will permit completion of the airfields by
                        May 15th.”</p>
                </quote>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RH1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">H. Redman</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                    <lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RFB1">F. B. <hi rend="smallcaps">Royal</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                    <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Combined Secretariat</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
